17 August 02<br>
&quot;Catch This&quot; by Joanna Symons<br>
<br>
Watch out for low-flying tomatoes if you're in the vicinity of Bunol, 30 miles from Valencia in Spain, when La Tomatina, the world's largest tomato war, erupts at the end of August each year in the Plaza del Pueblo.  Five rockets packed with tomatoes will be fired into the sky to mark the start of proceedings, after which some 30,000 locals and visitors will lob tomatoes at anything that moves, using the town's stockpile of more than 120 tons of squishy red ammo.<br>
<br>
Anyone can participate - and old clothes and goggles are recommended.  Protocol dictates that tomatoes must be squashed before they are thrown.  Any other missiles, such as water bombs or rotten eggs, are strictly banned.  Camera-wielding tourists are always prime targets, so buy a disposable camera if you want to record the occasion.  By 1pm, the battle is over, shopkeepers remove the plastic covers from their windows and a massive clean-up operation begins. <br>
<br>
There are various theories about the origins of the festival in 1944.  Some suggest it began as an anti-Franco protest; others say it dates from a skirmish between groups of friends that escalated into a tomato fight, with ammunition provided by a nearby market stall.  Everybody enjoyed the fracas so much, the story goes, that the event became an annual  fixture. <br>
<br>
However it started, La Tomatina is now the central event in a week-long fiesta when Bunol celebrates with parades, music, fireworks, and street parties in honour of Bunol's patron saint, San Luis Bertran, and the Virgin Mary. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uoliiasmoorglade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OliiasMoorglade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 388<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/6/02 10:20:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thephosphorbox.com/cptrply-small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weird tomato news from England</span><hr size=1> How about we have an FV gathering for a Cheeto-Bombardment Festival?<br>
